caption: One of the best places for sushi in St. Louis!
sushi, yeah, delicious. Great place to meet and catch up with friends. This place has a nice atmosphere. This place has great reviews for a reason.
A top spot for delicious sushi. Staff is always super even when they have a full house. Next time I'll be back with my coworkers.
Seriously great sushi and tempura. The milk tea is solid too and fast service. Easily a new spot for us to order from.
I bring my husband here each time we visit StL. He spent some time in Japan and says Sushi Koi is authentic sushi. We recommend Sushi Koi to everyone.
Best place for sushi! Chef Whitney is awesome! Always take good care of us, even if it's only pickup currently. Please go support your local small business!
Great Boba and service!
Find the freshest finest sushi in STL here with the upmost highest impeccable service & hospitality. Always a great menu with delicious tastes!! Thanks
The best sushi I have ever had, not just in STL, but everywhere! The spicy tuna and California rolls are my go to and the spice and quality of the tuna was superb!
Server was super chill and on point.  The rolls were great. Get the takoyaki! I've had it made by my Japanese friend (who is also a professionally trained chef) and it rivals hers

I was only in town for a few days and looking for some good sushi. Found it! this place was small but very good with a nice variety. The waiters were friendly and helpful. It was packed when we walked in but they quickly cleared off a table for us to sit and order.
Great food, excellent service!
Good Sushi and great company.
Sushi was warm, also i got a little sick a couple hours later, server was a nice guy and he took my wifes order off the reciept without us even asking.
Really good food, great environment and affordable parking garage across the street. I would suggest making a reservation though.

Hands down, the best sushi I've had in St Louis! I got a special roll with spicy tuna and eel, and it was delicious. The miso soup also has a good amount of flavor, and is only $2! Perfect side dish for a chilly night.
Best sushi in STL. Amazing happy hour specials. Small place, get there early.
Great lunch specials in this bustling little joint. Great service too.
Our first time at Sushi Koi. Excellent!! So fresh! Will be going back soon!!
Good Sushi
Awesome
Went for udon. Got hot sake, udon, and two spicy tuna hand rolls (because happy hour). Had an excellent experience. Will go again.
Really good sushi, and good prices especially during happy hour. Their lychee cocktail was really good, too.

I have frequented this restaurant several times after work in order to take advantage of the happy hour specials. The special prices begin at 4:30, which is great for a quick bite after work. The staff is always incredibly friendly, greeting patrons as they enter and offering warm smiles. Tako yaki is an incredible starter to the meal. It always comes out hot and flavorful. Good options from the happy hour menu that always arrive at the table tasting amazing are the eel maki rolls, spicy tuna maki rolls, and spicy tuna hand rolls.

Excellent place with amazing sushi!!! We are always looking for a place with good sushi, and Unfortunately Saint Louis does not have big choice. When we tried Sushi Koi... we knew we found a place where will be going regularly. We live in Saint Charles, but for that art of sushi at Sushi Koi, we don’t mind a drive:)
Such good sushi! Definitely recommend trying sushi koi out! 10 stars for customer service! Actually, best customer service I’ve had in awhile! Try them out you won’t regret it!
Great atmosphere. The salmon avocado roll and chicken bento box were delicious. Service was awesome! Definitely would recommend.
delicious!

I did NOT like sushi until I was introduced to this restaurant. It was amazing! One of my new favorite restaurants! The atmosphere was perfect for conversation. Our waiter was helpful and attentive but did not "over visit" our table. And the food.... Fresh... No fishy taste.... Perfection!!!

We've been twice so far. Each time the quality of fish used is amazing. The friends we brought were very pleased. The lobster roll is so good & I am in love with their lychee martini, wait to eat the lychee until the end! So good. But try to get there around open on the weekend nights. Friday night gets a bit tight.
Nice find in CWE.  Really liked the Hamachi garlic roll, dragon roll.

Really liked this place. Lots of great sushi options. I love a place that let's the seafood speak and not have every available roll covered in sauce or loaded with fried items or cream cheese. Nice work, Sushi Koi!

We went for lunch. My wife and I. There is outdoor seating but we opted for indoors. It's not really big but the space is not cramped. The staff were very friendly and hospitable and the standard sushi/sashimi offering were listed on the menu. I had a chirashi bowl. Lots of rice and the usual accompaniments. I was slightly (very slightly) disappointed in the sashimi in the bowl and I only say this because my usual sushi restaurant takes very good care of me  and likely adds a little extra. That said, it was more than filling especially with the amount of rice. I also had a sumo roll and a premium Sapporo. I would recommend this as the food, service and cleanliness were all of high standard. The downside.... Only one, unisex bathroom.

Service was quick and friendly.  I saw some pictures of the lobster roll from previous reviews and it did not disappoint.  The lobster was juicy and plentiful, the sashimi and sushi was fresh, and the soft shell crab was on point.  I wish I took more pictures but honestly everything was so good, I forgot to.
The eel unagi is excellent!
Solid sushi spot. Had some assorted sashimi and a unagi roll. Would definitely go again.
Wonderful people & food!
Quaint little hard to notice place with great sushi
EXCELLENT!! I'm far from my sunny shores of California and this place was awesome! Don't question it, just go!
Loved the sashimi there. Our waiter was really nice.
Great lunch specials!
Went with a group of friends and all of our friend was delicious. The portions are big and the prices are decent. Service was great and friendly.
The biggest rolls I've ever seen! The fish was all super fresh, and the server really know's his stuff. We will definitely be back.

Probably the best sushi I've had in the Midwest; presentation and quality has always been on point. Chef Whitney is a delight and both Justin and Charlie who frequently work during the weekdays are great guys and have always offered great service
Sushi was good. I ate outside on a perfect day.
Small place. Freindly place.  Great sushi. Clean.
Cooked food was delicious.
Great service, great food
A solid quick bite place. Good happy hour.
Food so so. The waiter who served me was quite pushy.
Phenomenal
Amazing food!
Best sushi I’ve ever had. Amazing 👌🏼
We ❤❤❤ the food,atmosphere and all the people that work there!!!
Had a great time eating up at the bar and chatting with Chef Whitney. Delicious sushi!  My waiter was very knowledgeable and on top of everything.  Will be back when traveling through St. Louis.

Over 30 minutes wait between appetizer and sushi rolls when the restaurant didn't seem that busy ... Dumplings were fine. Miso soup weirdly thick/over-powered. Ultimately just so-so sushi. Not worth the wait or price. Two stars because we're Midwest nice and the waiter seemed to feel bad about it all.
Amazing sushi, staff is fun and efficient, good mochi.

Probably the best sushi place in the Midwest. We tried around 12 different rolls and all of them were delicious. They have both traditional takes as well as some Americana classics. The drink menu is a bit limited, but the sushi more than makes up for it. prices are pretty reasonable on there is an abundance of street parking nearby. Team favorite was the lobster roll.
Great sushi. Downsides: can't bring more than 4 people realistically (small tables in a small space) and it's pricey.

Went here on a recommendation from fiends. It’s a small place and our first impression wasn’t 5 stars. We were BLOWN AWAY with the food. By far the best sushi in STL I’ve ever had. Our server was on point and we had instant service when we wanted it. Will be back.
Pricey but amazing sushi. Everything is great, my husband said it’s the best sushi he’s ever had and he’s very picky with sushi
By far the BEST sushi in St. Louis. My favorite is the Central West End roll, but everything here is top notch. Whitney is the chef, go see her and you won't be disappointed!!
Quality sushi for saint Louis and not that expensive

Some of the best sushi in the Central West End. Also on the pricey side. Service is Hit or Miss, they seem to have a lot of turnover and always be training new people who seem to be Clueless. I would give them 5 stars but they are very inconsistent with their hours not opening for dinner on time and closing early unexpectedly.

Hands down great sushi, and honestly one of the best happy hours around. And when I say great sushi, I mean both in freshness of fish and attention to detail. I ordered the salmon skin roll the other day and not only did it have delicious crunchy salmon skin but also pickled radish and kanpyo, which added really lovely for flavor and texture. Just unlike what you'll get at a lot of other sushi place.

This place rocks. Great service, great selection, and quick. Clean, and well kept. The speciality rolls we got were fantastic, and I'd venture to say you can't really go wrong here. The plates come out and they do a stellar job at presentation here. Instagram friendly (or something). Really awesome ice cream for dessert, too. Doesn't break the bank as bad as some other sushi places in town. Go all out! 🍣 🍣 🍣

Delicious sushi for the Midwest. The spicy tuna was actually spicy, the eel was just warm enough, and the crispy was actually crispy. If you're looking for a reasonably priced meal, go ahead and head there for happy hour and get some $3 rolls.
My favorite sushi spot in STL. Ask for fresh wasabi... It's pretty cool. Also, the Toro.
Good food good service
Best in St Louis!

Hopefully the painfully slow service was an anomaly. Sushi was ok but we finished most of our first roll before the second roll we ordered got there.  The server was not very attentive as our waters and beers were empty for most of our wait. The garlic roll sounded interesting so we ordered it but ended up disappointed.  It had no balance, it was all heat because the 1/4 inch thick jalapeño slices on top. I’d order it again but ask for more thinly sliced peppers on top or maybe omitted all together.
Delicious!
Best sushi I’ve had in STL

I have lived in CWE for two years and had never been to Sushi Koi until recently. I usually opt for Kampai or Sub Zero, but after my experience here I will make this my regular sushi stop. Not only was the restaurant atmosphere clean and sleek, but the food and service were great! The price of sushi here is much lower than other places nearby and the same, if not better, quality. Our waiter was really nice, but our food took a while to come out. Because of this, he offered us complementary dumplings, which was so great! I believe our waiter's name was Ryan, but am not completely sure. Whoever he was, he was very friendly, accommodating and hardworking. We truly enjoyed our experience here and will be back.
Pretty good and good setvice!!

Friendly atmosphere. Food is excellent. Service was awesome. They explain everything to you if you've not had the type of food before. Small cozy place. Even the tea was the best I've had in a long time. We will be eating there again for sure.
Pretty good sushi and stuff for people who don't like raw fish
Very pleasant experience. Food was delish. Service was great. Mostly 4 tops but we had a party of 8 and were accommodated without issue.
Best sushi in the Central Wesr End, and I'v tried all of them. It also has a fantastic lunch special from 11 to 2pm.
Best sushi on the central west end
Great food and great atmosphere. Delicious soup, chicken, pot stickers and best sushi I've had.

Went to sushi Kio this past weekend and got food poisoning. Be cautions of this place. I ordered the Philadelphia roll and the California roll. So not sure which one got me sick. But it was 24 hrs of hell.  Hope this never happens to anyone else that goes here.
Lunch specials are great.  4 pieces on salmon sushi and a roll of your choice for $11 and it tastes great every time. Or, you can choose 2 rolls for $12.
my fav in the cwe
10/10 quality of fish. Sashimi Deluxe was an absolute pleasure, and the prices are reasonable. Cozy yet contemporary.
Great happy hour prices

The waitstaff are super friendly, and the food is incredible. I highly recommend tako yaki and the dragon roll, but I’ve had other stuff here and honestly it’s all  great. For the quality you get, the prices are unbelievable.
Loved it.... Was my first time going but i will be back for happy hour!!
Good prices, good sushi.
Really great sushi!
I love sushi koi. I ABSOLUTELY LOVE SUSHI KOI. This place has great food and is 2nd to none. Everytime i go my eyes are bigger then my stomach. Everything is sooo fire. Can't wait to return.
Amazing food. Best sushi I've ever had. The owners are great people and the restaurant itself has a good vibe to it. Love this place. Only sushi place I'll eat at now.

Small restaurant near BJC. Excellent service and nice selection of sushi rolls. The toro we ordered tasted fishy, so it was not fresh. Also a few other selections had same issue. So we were not able to fully enjoy the sushi.
Great sushi with multiple vegan options.

Easily the best sushi in St. Louis/CWE/Greater St Louis area. Before coming to St Louis for school, I waitressed at multiple sushi restaurants and have eaten at dozens of sushi restaurants from California to Boston; this little cozy place is easily the best. The fish here is always fresh and available for very reasonable prices. Having worked at other places, I know that a lot of sushi restaurants will often skimp on the fish in the lunch/happy hour rolls but at Koi, they’re always super generous with their cuts. Yes, there may only be one sushi chef (the owner) so it might not be great for large parties, but the chef really does put her heart into every cut of fish and roll. I think there was a week where I ate here for lunch almost every day... Staff always does a great job!
Great sushi, average prices for the area. It always tastes fresh and good customer service!
Went for happy hour with friends... staff was friendly and atmosphere was nice as well.. tried octopus for the first time.. smoked.. was actually really good.. will definitely go again
Fantastic food!  Price is very reasonable.  One of the best in STL.
Solid happy hour special, and fresh sushi
Excellent!
Great sushi. A little pricy, cozy is a good word for a little cramped and we'll used.

Fairly standard sushi. They have very fresh wasabi which was a great surprise (especially seeing the wife discover it). All nigiri were good quality, but the tuna was a bit rubber like. Uni was on point and the server knew good details about it. The Hamachi roll (2nd picture) is a big portion which is reflected in the price. Not complicated in flavors, but a joy to eat. Service was great and very up front about their toro (where others try to pass chu-toro as o-toro or not even know what toro is even if it's on their menu). Sushi chef was very nice as well. I am happy with my experience here and is a good base to check out other sushi restaurants.
Loved the veggie roll and vegan sushi!
Food was a little pricey, but their lunch combo was a decent deal and the food was amazing.
Great sushi and awesome lunch specials!
Nice little place to go for lunch.  Told them it was my first time there and came away with a free dessert.  Staff was wonderful!
Service was not good. But the food was great
It's  so nice and delicious Yam  yam and healthy
Great Sushi and very friendly service
Great lunch spot. Good food and service.

(Translated by Google) Super good service and very tasty and well presented food. We ate gyosa, sushimi, rolls: red bird roll, euclid, west central and others. all very rich  (Original) super buena atención y la comida muy rica y bien presentada. comimos gyosa, sushimi, rolls: red bird roll, euclid, west central y otros.  todo muy rico
Just went for sushi and it was worth it, so good and grey price for two. Husband and I got two rolls and sake was tasty too. Definitly going back.

This place is phenomenal. The best sushi I've had in St Louis. I got the chirashi don and takoyaki to start, and they were both perfect. The takoyaki was crispy on the outside, and warm and gooey once I bit into it, and they did not skimp on the squid. Most sushi joints here don't even have it on the menu, but Sushi Koi just nails it. The chirashi don - I haven't had raw fish this good in St Louis. The temperature of the fish was room temperature. It melted in my mouth like butter. I was sad toward the end of my meal because I realized that once I had a certain piece, I couldn't have it again. It was that good. All in all, I would highly recommend this place to anyone that loves quality sushi.
Best in town
Best sushi you will ever eat!!!  Too bad the management of the kitchen is lacking.
The best sushi around.

Freshest, tastiest sushi!  Not too expensive, especially for the amount of fish. Other restaurants add a lot of rice to the roll.  Sushi Koi packs the fish and only a thin layer of well-seasoned rice on the roll.  You won't be disappointed.
Service is very seriously lacking.
Best sushi in Saint Louis. The sushi chef is the owner. Very talented
Decently priced sushi. Sushi is pretty good and friendly service. Half hour menu is good.

I absolutely loved this place. Our waitress picked out our sake and sushi for us because we figured she would know best and boy did she! We sat at the bar so we could chat with our sushi chef Whitney a bit. She was amazing. Jovial and friendly even though she was working her ass off to make us the best sushi I've ever had! Period.Try the sumo roll and the dinamite roll if you like a little kick. Every bite was like a slice of heaven in your mouth. I almost cried with joy.
Decent priced sushi, friendly staff, and a nice environment 😊
Love the sushi happy hour. The sushi is delicious and the service is friendly. I have been visiting my nephew at Children's Hospital and it's a great break from hospital food.
Food was excellent and the service amazing, bright and attentive
Awesome food!!! Definitely best sushi in town!
Everytime I come here I fall more in love with the food. The service is great and the sushi, and chief, is the best in STL in my opinion. Will always recommend you guys to other people. Keep it up!
Our waiter was perfect and the  fish was so fresh tasting. Everthing was presented well, and our expert waiter brought it out with ideal timing. Best hamachi kama I have had in STL.
Very friendly service and the most high quality sushi you'll find in St. Louis at a great price.

My favorite sushi joint in STL. The sushi selection is great and delicious, the have the best spicy baked muscles, and then I always leave with a matcha boba green tea. The space is tight but I've always felt comfortable and they keep the atmosphere upbeat and cool. I couldn't ask for more from a sushi restaurant. 😀

My friend and I dropped by this place for a weekend lunch.When my party arrived, there were already nine parties waiting outside in front of us. Good first sign. Surprisingly, the line shortened rather quickly and we got in within minutes. I ordered the Extra Special Cheshire Bowl. It came with a bowl of miso soup, which was perfect in the cold weather. A few minutes later, the waiter brought the main course over. The Hashim were thick and tasted fresh several pieces simply melted in my mouth. The tam ago was a tad sweet, but otherwise was pretty good. The sushi rice was perfect--at the right grainy texture with the right amount of sushi vinegar. $29 still felt a bit expensive, but it was certainly worth it the first time.
Whitney is the best can't wait to get there
Great Happy Hour prices! Best sushi I've had in St. Louis, and fast, professional service.

I dropped into Chi Sushi (new name, same location) while in CWE and — WOW! I totally underestimated how good the sushi and service would be! We were warmly greeted, then they explained exactly what they had to offer without looking frustrated with us. The lunch specials were large portions, too! The sushi tasted great and was very fresh. You just can't get better service and sushi than at Chi Sushi! We'll be coming back often!
so yummy!  good menu selection.
Wonderful service and absolutely delish food. Great lunch specials that include salad and Miso soup!

This is the best spot for lunchtime sushi in the CWE area.  They have an $11 lunch special and a punch card (buy 8 get 9th free).  High quality product, friendly staff and quick service (most of the time). I knocked one star off because I've had a couple times where I had to flag down someone for my check but that's not the norm.
(Translated by Google) Especially delicious, the first village of the Holy Village!  (Original) 特别好吃  圣村第一🍣！

Excellent service, tasty good, and fun artwork make this an awesome spot.  I've been twice to far and the waiter seemed genuinely happy to seat me and take my order.  The food was out quick, the drinks were out quicker, and both were really good.  It's a small place, but there were just enough people in there to keep it from being classified as "dead."  The artwork is really unique, when you go there you'll see what I mean, and it has one of the coolest bathrooms I've ever been in.  The only drawback is that if you don't go during the superb happy hour, the place can get expensive.
Horrible service
Excellent food & very helpful staff.
Food was good, but the waitress was very rude...

Great food kind of pricey but it assures the quality of the fish. Will definitely be going back as the food was fresh and tasted great. To the other two mentioned comments if you order a soft shell crab roll of course it'll be warm considering it's cooked. Go to schnucks for your sushi since you know nothing about quality. Service was also great here.

Under new managment, no longer fun techno atmosphere, very sterile, TWICE the price 4 roles was fifty bucks. Served us warm sushi and the spider roll tasted heavily of fish almost to where I spat it out!!!! Never going back and as many people over 10 years I told to go to old chi I WILL spend the next 10 telling people not to go to the new one

New ownership!!! Beware!  I miss the old chi. The restaurant itself is no longer fun and colorful, very bland and minalla. New owners and sushi chef. They served us warm and OFF rolls. One straight up tasted like warm fish! We mentioned this to the waiter, didnt eat the roll but they still charged us for it. We will never go back. Dont waste your time. 😥
Very good sushi.  A bit on the pricy side but well  worth it
Great place and worth the drive from MoFallon. Sushi chef is awesome.
Very good

I tried their soup that was on the appetizers because it was VERY cheap, and I wanted something to hold me over, and to my surprise it was exceptional. I would recommend this place over all other sushi restaurants.
